comments: Bridges (PHX) and Clarkson (UTA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs prior to the screen being set.
Vanderbilt (UTA) firms up with his right shoulder and does not deliver illegal contact to Bridges (PHX) during the screen.
Vanderbilt (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Booker's (PHX) path and he does not deliver contact.
Vanderbilt (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Bridges' (PHX) path and he does not deliver contact.
Conley (UTA) reaches in and initiates contact with Booker's (PHX) body and affects his ability to maintain possession of the ball while in the post.
Craig (PHX) and Markkanen (UTA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Bridges (PHX) is moving alongside Clarkson's (UTA) path and marginal body contact occurs during Clarkson's (UTA) drive.
Ayton (PHX) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with Vanderbilt (UTA) and incidental contact occurs as Vanderbilt (UTA) attempts to move over the screen.
Clarkson (UTA) jumps alongside Bridges (PHX) and marginal body contact occurs during Bridges's (PHX) upward shooting motion and play at the basket.
Vanderbilt (UTA) is drawn into the air on the pump fake and makes lower body contact with Ayton, which affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Payne (PHX) and Beasley (UTA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs prior to the pick being set.
Booker (PHX) places both hands on Markkanen's (UTA) back and marginal contact occurs at the end of Markkanen's drive.
Payne (PHX) extends a hand and marginal contact occurs with Markkanen's (UTA) arm as Markkanen gathers the ball.
Conley (UTA) briefly extends both hands and marginal contact occurs during Payne's drive.
Craig (PHX) briefly places his forearm into Markkanen's (UTA) front and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Olynyk (UTA) legally contests and avoids making contact with Lee's (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Lee (PHX) extends his leg into Olynyk (UTA), but the marginal contact does not affect his ability to defend the play.
